1. Overview

This document defines the complete GoHighLevel (GHL) setup for:

🚗 Garage Services Website

🚙 Car Sales Website

🏢 Same business entity

🔐 One GHL Sub-Account

👤 One controlled client portal login

The objective:

Keep both business lines separated internally

Maintain automation control

Provide a clean client-facing operational portal

Prevent workflow conflicts

Create a scalable foundation

2. System Architecture
SUB-ACCOUNT
├── PIPELINE: GARAGE – Services
├── PIPELINE: SALES – Vehicles
├── WORKFLOWS: GARAGE – ...
├── WORKFLOWS: SALES – ...
├── FORMS: GARAGE – ...
├── FORMS: SALES – ...
├── CALENDAR: GARAGE – Service Booking
├── CALENDAR: SALES – Test Drive
└── TAGS separated by prefix

All assets must be prefixed clearly to prevent system overlap.

3. Snapshot Loading Strategy
Step 1 — Load Garage Snapshot

Immediately rename all assets:

Pipeline → GARAGE – Services

Workflows → GARAGE – [Workflow Name]

Forms → GARAGE – Service Form

Tags → GARAGE – MOT, GARAGE – Repair

Calendar → GARAGE – Service Booking

Step 2 — Load Dealer Snapshot

Rename all assets:

Pipeline → SALES – Vehicles

Workflows → SALES – [Workflow Name]

Forms → SALES – Vehicle Enquiry

Tags → SALES – Finance, SALES – Hot

Calendar → SALES – Test Drive

Never leave generic names.

